<title type="html"><![CDATA[Super Mario World Famicom pirate]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5568&amp;p=50631#p50631"><![CDATA[
From what I understand (I don't have any mapper 90 carts) they use a 'glob-top' package for those mappers, and in that case it almost always follows that the ROMs are glob-top also.  To quote the magic 8-ball, "outlook not good".  Even so, it's theoretically still possible, but it would be a lot of work (you could scape off the solder-mask and wire to some thin traces on the PCB - assuming all of them are exposed and not under the epoxy blob).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Mon Sep 14, 2009 6:56 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
